http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: common title for a collection of resources where title identifies elements of a series collectively, combined with information about what volumes are available at the source cite
reference from one resource to another

inverse of wasGeneratedBy where the domain resource generated the range resoure implying that the domain resource is a temporal event, such as a data processing action, and the range resource is an entity
inverse of wasDerivedFrom where the range resource was derived from the domain resource
reference to resources that are parts of this resource
reference to a master resource of which this one is a part

inverse of operatesOn where the domain resource is, or can be, operated on (queried, subsetted etc.) by the range resource which must be an agent (i.e. is something that bears some form of responsibility for the operation taking place)
an equivalent relationship to srv:operatesOn from a Service to a Dataset
part of same structured set of data held in a computer
resource is a revision of associated resource
associated through a common heritage such as produced to a common product specification
part of a set of imagery that when used together, provides three-dimensional images
the domain resource was derived from the range resource which must have been an entity (i.e. not an actor with agency or a temporal event)
the domain resource was generated by the range resource which must have been a temporal event such as a data processing action or a field survey

The domain resource was informed by the range resource which must have been an Entity (i.e. not an Agent with agency or an Activity temporal event).

This is a looser association than wasDerivedFrom and does not indicate direct derivation, as wasDerivedFrom does.
